:S156 :hasReference :R111 .
:S156 :hasReference :R112 .
:S156 :hasSubstanceDescription "Naproxen helps relieve inflammation and pain associated with muscle, joint or tendon disorders.; Chloroquine is used to prevent and treat malaria. It is also used to treat liver infection caused by protozoa (extraintestinal amebiasis)." .

:S157 :hasSubstanceDescription "Opioids are common, effective painkillers. But healthcare providers use them cautiously because of the possible side effects. Examples of common opioid medications include codeine, fentanyl, and hydrocodone." .
:S157 :hasReference :R113 .

:S158 :hasSubstanceDescription "ETHACRYNIC ACID reduces swelling related to heart, kidney, liver, or lung disease. It may also be used to reduce swelling caused by cancer. It helps your kidneys remove more fluid and salt from your blood through the urine. It belongs to a group of medications called diuretics." .
:S158 :hasReference :R145 .

:S159 :hasReference :R148 .
:S159 :hasSubstanceDescription "FUROSEMIDE treats high blood pressure. It may also be used to reduce swelling related to heart, kidney, or liver disease. It helps your kidneys remove more fluid and salt from your blood through the urine. It belongs to a group of medications called diuretics." .

:S160 :hasReference :R150 .
:S160 :hasSubstanceDescription "(warfarin, dicumarol, phenprocoumon, acenocumarol), interfering with vitamin K-dependent coagulation factors, are of benefit in the prevention of thromboembolic events when indicated, but concomitantly increase hemorrhagic risk." .

:S161 :hasReference :R151 .
:S161 :hasSubstanceDescription "used to manage and treat epilepsy, trigeminal neuralgia, and acute manic and mixed episodes in bipolar I disorder." .

:S162 :hasReference :R152 .
:S162 :hasSubstanceDescription "An antibiotic medication used to treat a variety of serious infections caused by bacteria but carries a high risk of causing serious bone marrow problems and is not frequently used." .

:S163 :hasReference :R153 .
