:SP159 :hasStewardshipDescription "Only take nitrofurantoin if a healthcare provider confirms or strongly suspects a urinary tract infection. Avoid using it for viral infections or other conditions where it won't help, to prevent antibiotic resistance and side effects." .
:SP159 :hasReference :R157 .

:SP160 :hasStewardshipDescription "Always finish the full prescribed course of nitrofurantoin, even if you start feeling better. Stopping early can allow bacteria to survive, potentially causing the infection to come back and increasing the chance of resistance." .
:SP160 :hasReference :R158 .

:SP161 :hasStewardshipDescription "Keep track of any unusual symptoms such as breathing difficulties, chest pain, cough, or numbness and tingling in the hands or feet. Report these promptly to a healthcare provider to prevent serious complicaions." .
:SP161 :hasReference :R159 .

:SP162 :hasStewardshipDescription "Do not share your nitrofurantoin with other people, even if they have similar symptoms. Using someone else's medicine can be unsafe and may contribute to ineffective treatment or antibiotic resistance." .
:SP162 :hasReference :R158 .

:SP163 :hasReference :R157 .
:SP163 :hasStewardshipDescription "Store nitrofurantoin in a cool, dry place at room temperature, away from direct sunlight, moisture, or heat. Proper storage helps maintain the effectiveness and safety of the medication throughout its shelf life." .

:SP164 :hasStewardshipDescription "Take Macrobid only for urinary infections proven or strongly suspected; do not use for colds or other viruses." .
:SP164 :hasReference :R160 .

:SP165 :hasReference :R160 .
:SP165 :hasStewardshipDescription "Complete the full course of medicine even if symptoms improve, to prevent infection from coming back and bacteria from becoming resistant." .

